{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775874900906,"sessionID":"ses_2859c19c1ffeZ9El7LkVpI02HE","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6483a70011ydihxLlPTZSI3","messageID":"msg_d7a64761b001oyUZ8gtPFhf7hj","sessionID":"ses_2859c19c1ffeZ9El7LkVpI02HE","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775874937439,"sessionID":"ses_2859c19c1ffeZ9El7LkVpI02HE","part":{"id":"prt_d7a648c93001TZUAJXf9BmH744","messageID":"msg_d7a64761b001oyUZ8gtPFhf7hj","sessionID":"ses_2859c19c1ffeZ9El7LkVpI02HE","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_2961a98f2a564c42a4955824","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing multi-stage Docker builds for AgentCube server components, creating 3 optimized container images using shared build infrastructure.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-032\n- **Module**: `docker`\n- **Language**: `Dockerfile`\n- **Size**: S\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Docker Directory Structure\n\n### AR-032-001: Docker directory creation\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n- **WHEN** creating docker module directory\n- **THEN** it SHALL be located at `docker/`\n- **AND** SHALL contain base.Dockerfile and component Dockerfiles\n\n### AR-032-002: Base Dockerfile structure\n\n- **GIVEN** docker directory\n- **WHEN** creating base build stage\n- **THEN** it SHALL be named `base.Dockerfile`\n- **AND** SHALL provide shared Go build environment\n- **AND** SHALL use golang:1.24-alpine as base image\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Base Build Stage\n\n### AR-032-003: Go toolchain installation\n\n- **GIVEN** base.Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** building the base image\n- **THEN** it SHALL include Go 1.24 toolchain\n- **AND** SHALL cache go.mod/go.sum dependencies\n\n### AR-032-004: Build artifacts preparation\n\n- **GIVEN** base build stage\n- **WHEN** executing build\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile binaries for linux/amd64\n- **AND** SHALL produce statically linked binaries (CGO_ENABLED=0)\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Router Dockerfile\n\n### AR-032-005: Router multi-stage build\n\n- **GIVEN** docker/Dockerfile.router\n- **WHEN** building router image\n- **THEN** it SHALL use multi-stage build pattern\n- **AND** SHALL copy binary from builder stage\n- **AND** SHALL use alpine:3.19 as runtime base\n\n### AR-032-006: Router runtime configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** router runtime container\n- **WHEN** container starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL run as non-root user (UID 1000)\n- **AND** SHALL have binary at `/usr/local/bin/router`\n- **AND** SHALL expose HTTP port (configurable)\n\n### AR-032-007: Router image size\n\n- **GIVEN** built router image\n- **WHEN** checking image size\n- **THEN** it SHALL be approximately 25-30MB\n- **AND** SHALL not exceed 50MB\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Workload Manager Dockerfile\n\n### AR-032-008: Workload Manager multi-stage build\n\n- **GIVEN** docker/Dockerfile.workload-manager\n- **WHEN** building workload-manager image\n- **THEN** it SHALL use multi-stage build pattern\n- **AND** SHALL copy binary from builder stage\n- **AND** SHALL use alpine:3.19 as runtime base\n\n### AR-032-009: Workload Manager runtime configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** workload-manager runtime container\n- **WHEN** container starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL run as non-root user (UID 1000)\n- **AND** SHALL have binary at `/usr/local/bin/workload-manager`\n- **AND** SHALL accept Redis configuration via environment variables\n\n### AR-032-010: Workload Manager image size\n\n- **GIVEN** built workload-manager image\n- **WHEN** checking image size\n- **THEN** it SHALL be approximately 30-35MB\n- **AND** SHALL not exceed 50MB\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Agentd Dockerfile\n\n### AR-032-011: Agentd multi-stage build\n\n- **GIVEN** docker/Dockerfile.agentd\n- **WHEN** building agentd image\n- **THEN** it SHALL use multi-stage build pattern\n- **AND** SHALL include both agentd and picod binaries\n- **AND** SHALL use alpine:3.19 as runtime base\n\n### AR-032-012: Agentd runtime configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** agentd runtime container\n- **WHEN** container starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL run as non-root user (UID 1000)\n- **AND** SHALL have agentd at `/usr/local/bin/agentd`\n- **AND** SHALL have picod at `/usr/local/bin/picod`\n\n### AR-032-013: Agentd image size\n\n- **GIVEN** built agentd image\n- **WHEN** checking image size\n- **THEN** it SHALL be approximately 35-40MB\n- **AND** SHALL not exceed 60MB\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Makefile Integration\n\n### AR-032-014: Build all images target\n\n- **GIVEN** Makefile\n- **WHEN** running `make docker-build`\n- **THEN** it SHALL build router, workload-manager, and agentd images\n- **AND** SHALL tag each with `:latest` tag\n\n### AR-032-015: Individual build targets\n\n- **GIVEN** Makefile\n- **WHEN** running `make docker-build-router`\n- **THEN** it SHALL build only router image\n- **AND** similar pattern for workload-manager and agentd\n\n### AR-032-016: Push targets\n\n- **GIVEN** Makefile\n- **WHEN** running `make docker-push`\n- **THEN** it SHALL push all 3 images to registry\n- **AND** SHALL push each tagged image\n\n### AR-032-017: Image naming convention\n\n- **GIVEN** built images\n- **WHEN** listing image tags\n- **THEN** router SHALL be named `agentcube-router:latest`\n- **AND** workload-manager SHALL be named `agentcube-workload-manager:latest`\n- **AND** agentd SHALL be named `agentcube-agentd:latest`\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Build Validation\n\n### AR-032-018: Binary execution\n\n- **GIVEN** built router image\n- **WHEN** running `docker run --rm agentcube-router version`\n- **THEN** it SHALL output version information\n- **AND** exit with code 0\n\n### AR-032-019: Non-root execution\n\n- **GIVEN** any built container\n- **WHEN** checking user inside container\n- **THEN** it SHALL NOT run as root (UID 0)\n- **AND** SHALL use UID 1000\n\n### AR-032-020: Multi-stage layers verification\n\n- **GIVEN** built image\n- **WHEN** running `docker history`\n- **THEN** it SHALL show builder stage layers\n- **AND** SHALL show runtime stage layers\n- **AND** builder stage SHALL NOT be in final image\n\n### AR-032-021: Build cache reuse\n\n- **GIVEN** previously built image\n- **WHEN** rebuilding with no code changes\n- **THEN** it SHALL use cached layers\n- **AND** SHALL complete in under 30 seconds\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Security\n\n### AR-032-022: Minimal runtime image\n\n- **GIVEN** runtime container\n- **WHEN** listing installed packages\n- **THEN** it SHALL only contain Alpine base packages\n- **AND** SHALL NOT contain build tools (gcc, make, etc.)\n\n### AR-032-023: No sensitive data in image\n\n- **GIVEN** built images\n- **WHEN** inspecting filesystem\n- **AND** SHALL NOT contain go.mod or go.sum files\n- **AND** SHALL NOT contain source code\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Compatibility\n\n### AR-032-024: Build context compatibility\n\n- **GIVEN** project root as build context\n- **WHEN** running docker build\n- **THEN** it SHALL successfully copy all required files\n- **AND** SHALL handle go modules correctly\n\n### AR-032-025: Binary compatibility\n\n- **GIVEN** compiled binaries\n- **WHEN** running on alpine runtime\n- **THEN** binaries SHALL be statically linked\n- **AND** SHALL NOT require glibc\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Docker multi-stage builds documentation\n- Alpine Linux container best practices\n- AgentCube design: `design.md`\n- AR-030: Helm chart (downstream consumer)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775874937429,"end":1775874937437}}}}
